<br>
What is Evil?<br>
<br>
<br>
Is &quot;evil&quot; in the rping sense total hate, violence, and wrath to all?  Is it a kindred with those hated by the &quot;lights&quot; and the reciprocation of that hate from them?<br>
<br>
Or is it simply propaganda forced on us by the lights who see us as a threat to their way of life.  Are we just free beings who can do as we please, and in our freedom are called blasphemous and hatefull by those who do not possess that freedom.<br>
<br>
As &quot;evil&quot; characters we can basically kill anything in this world with little care as to what it affects.  A druid for example is shunned for kiling anything of nature(we are stricktly talking rping here.)  But a darkie can kill anything, now it is not benificial to kill eachother, but we can do it.  <br>
<br>
I know &quot;evil&quot; characters who hold themselves to higher moral codes than some paladins.  Who is more &quot;evil?&quot; They do not swear, fool around, or talk down to light races.  The difference being they uphold those morals because they want to, not because they &quot;have to.&quot;  <br>
<br>
When innoruuk took the first away from the lights and took them with him, he did not torture them like all the history says. He simply desocialized them.  He brought them to a place where they could choose their own path.  They worshiped him for their new freedom and he even gave some power over the dead(seen by some as power over death(not the same)) <br>
<br>
Once the lights saw the freedom we have, they began to hate us.  They have hated us since that time, and because of that many of us have not bore the weight and clinged on to that hate and became what they call &quot;evil.&quot;  <br>
<br>
I have never been one to turn away those in need.  I have helped the darks and lights equally.  Does that make me &quot;good?&quot;  I hold no bitterness, no &quot;hate&quot; towards any others, does that make me &quot;just?&quot;  <br>
<br>
I can control fear yes, and i can control the dead, but I am free of the two.  I am their master not the other way around.  For those who dont' understand that power, they see it as a terrible way. But why?  It is because they themselves have been brought up to belive that.  <br>
<br>
I was brought up to belive that &quot;lights&quot; were themselves blasphemous.  I then learned that they are bound by what they belive, we are set free.  Their bitterness to our freedom has caused all this mess.  <br>
<br>
It is written, &quot;do not be comformed to the world, but transformed by the renewing of your mind.&quot;  <br>
<br>
We are not bound to the rules of the &quot;lights.&quot;  Let them hate us for our power, for our wisdom, and our Master. But let us be pure in action, and blameless to this world. If they hate us for our freedom, and our power, let them.  If their jelousy burns them up inside, let it. <br>
<br>
Let them slice their own throute, in their hatred for us. <br>
<br>
But, if they can disregard thier own beliefs and join us in our freedom, release their inner turmoil, then let us accept them into us.  <br>
<br>
<br>
As a Prophet of Innoruuk, and a Member of Midnight Council, I bid you hope, peace, and freedom. May your path be strewn with the dead of those who cast themselves away in want of us. May the numbers of those who have been set free grow each day. <p><center>
